<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Formula Diagram</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Formula Diagram</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When a valid formula has been entered in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Formula_Text_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Formula text box</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Formula_Editor" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Formula Editor</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Formula diagram</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> displays the formula in a hierarchical view using a tree control. When collapsed, each node of the tree shows either an </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Operators" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">operator</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Functions" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">function</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the name of a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Sets_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">data set</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Global_Variables_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">global variable</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, or a constant along with the arguments on which the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Operators" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">operator</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Functions" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">function</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> acts. In the case of a function, this is followed by two colons and the function prototype which helps the user determine the purpose of each argument. Nodes for </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Operators" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">operators</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Functions" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">functions</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be expanded. When expanded, each daughter node displays one of the arguments for the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Operators" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">operator</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Functions" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">function</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
